# KonceptOS

**Formal Concept Analysis as a Development Operating System**

K = (G, M, I) where G = modules, M = data channels, I : G × M → {0, R, W, RW}.

All I values are hypotheses. Refine RW → R/W/0. This IS program design.

## What it does

KonceptOS extracts a formal structure (K) from requirements, then uses that structure to:
- Generate runtime framework code mechanically from K
- Guide LLM to implement modules one at a time, constrained by contracts
- Verify implementations against K (contract violations, multi-writer conflicts)
- Assemble all modules into a runnable application

## Quick Start

```bash
export OPENROUTER_API_KEY="sk-or-v1-..."

python main.py
# or
python -m konceptos

# Load saved state
python main.py --load state.json
```

## Workflow

```
llm analyze spec.md        → Extract K₀ from requirements
resolve obj|attr <id>       → Refine K (split objects/attributes)
schema auto all             → Auto-generate TypeScript schemas
impl <module>               → LLM generates one module (with framework context)
verify                      → Check impls against K contracts
assemble game.html          → Mechanical assembly (no LLM)
```

## Project Structure

```
konceptos/
  engine.py         K engine (G/M/I, FCA, DAG, resolve)
  codegen.py        Code generation (framework.js, impl context, assemble)
  verify.py         Verification & K feedback (contract violations, multi-writer)
  llm.py            LLM prompt templates and API calls
  seed.py           Pluggable prior knowledge (Seed/JsonSeed/SeedChain)
  cli.py            REPL commands
  util.py           Shared utilities
main.py             Entry point
```

## Key Concepts

| Concept | Meaning |
|---------|---------|
| G (Objects) | Modules — things that DO something |
| M (Attributes) | Data channels — concrete data flowing between modules |
| I (Incidence) | Who does what on which channel: 0/R/W/RW |
| RW | Top — "might be involved, direction unknown" |
| W | Controls — reads old value + writes new value |
| DAG | Immutable version history, content-addressable |
| Seed | Prior knowledge at decision points |

## vs Traditional Development

Traditional: dependencies implicit, interface changes require guessing impact.
KonceptOS: all dependencies explicit in I matrix, diff mechanically lists affected modules.

## vs Current AI Coding

Current AI: generate → test → patch loop. No structural memory. Architecture drifts silently.
KonceptOS: I matrix is persistent structural memory. Architecture is first-class. LLM writes code, K maintains consistency.

